  "local_port": 50536,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are some karaoke songs for a 2nd alto?",
  "response": "Choosing the right karaoke song can enhance your performance and ensure you feel confident while singing. As a 2nd alto, you typically have a rich, lower female vocal range. Here are some karaoke-friendly songs that suit an alto voice, spanning various genres and styles:\n\n### **Pop Hits**\n1. **Adele \u2013 \"Someone Like You\"**\n   - A soulful ballad that highlights lower vocal tones.\n2. **Ariana Grande \u2013 \"Almost Is Never Enough\"**\n   - A duet that allows for expressive vocal delivery within a comfortable range.\n3. **Alicia Keys \u2013 \"If I Ain't Got You\"**\n   - Smooth and emotive, perfect for showcasing vocal depth.\n\n### **Classic Favorites**\n1. **Aretha Franklin \u2013 \"Respect\"**\n   - Empowering and powerful, great for strong vocal expression.\n2. **Etta James \u2013 \"At Last\"**\n   - A timeless classic that highlights rich, lower registers.\n3. **Carole King \u2013 \"It's Too Late\"**\n   - Melodic and expressive, fitting for an alto\u2019s range.\n\n### **R&B and Soul**\n1. **Sade \u2013 \"No Ordinary Love\"**\n   - Smooth and sultry, ideal for conveying emotion.\n2. **Whitney Houston \u2013 \"Greatest Love of All\"**\n   - Inspirational with a comfortable vocal range for altos.\n3. **En Vogue \u2013 \"Don't Let Go (Love)\"**\n   - Powerful and rhythmic, suitable for dynamic performances.\n\n### **Rock and Indie**\n1. **Evanescence \u2013 \"Bring Me to Life\"**\n   - Combines melodic verses with powerful choruses, fitting for versatile altos.\n2. **Alanis Morissette \u2013 \"You Oughta Know\"**\n   - Energetic and expressive, allowing for passionate delivery.\n3. **Fleetwood Mac \u2013 \"Dreams\"**\n   - Mellow and rhythmic, perfect for a relaxed performance.\n\n### **Musical Theatre Favorites**\n1. **\"I Dreamed a Dream\" from *Les Mis\u00e9rables***\n   - Emotionally charged and showcases vocal depth.\n2. **\"Defying Gravity\" from *Wicked***\n   - Powerful and uplifting, great for dynamic altos.\n3. **\"Part of Your World\" from *The Little Mermaid***\n   - Melodic and expressive, fitting for a heartfelt rendition.\n\n### **Country and Folk**\n1. **Kacey Musgraves \u2013 \"Rainbow\"**\n   - Gentle and uplifting, ideal for a soothing performance.\n2. **Dolly Parton \u2013 \"Jolene\"**\n   - Storytelling with a strong melody, suitable for altos.\n3. **Taylor Swift \u2013 \"Shake It Off\"**\n   - Upbeat and fun, offering a range that's comfortable for altos.\n\n### **Jazz and Blues**\n1. **Billie Holiday \u2013 \"Blue Moon\"**\n   - Classic jazz standards that highlight lower vocal tones.\n2. **Norah Jones \u2013 \"Don't Know Why\"**\n   - Smooth and mellow, perfect for relaxed singing.\n3. **Amy Winehouse \u2013 \"Back to Black\"**\n   - Soulful with a rich vocal range, fitting for expressive altos.\n\n### **Tips for Choosing the Right Song:**\n- **Know Your Range:** Select songs that sit comfortably within your vocal range to avoid straining.\n- **Emotion and Story:** Choose songs that resonate with you emotionally, allowing for a more authentic performance.\n- **Practice:** Familiarize yourself with the song beforehand to ensure you're comfortable with the melody and lyrics.\n- **Original Key:** Consider performing songs in their original key or adjust them if needed to better suit your voice.\n\n### **Final Thoughts**\nUltimately, the best karaoke song for you is one that you enjoy and feel confident performing. Don\u2019t be afraid to experiment with different genres and styles to find what suits your unique alto voice best. Have fun and let your personality shine through your performance!",
